title: 2008 Republican Michigan Primary Vote count, Michigan by County , 16th Jan, 2008 at 00.10 hrs
name: 2008 Republican Michigan Primary Vote count, Michigan by County , 16th Jan, 2008 at 00.10 hrs
description: These maps are based on the Michigan Secretary of State Election Website (1) as of 10 minutes past Midnight, January 16, 2008. These are uncertified" results. This is Romney's first win and probably saved him from dropping out of the primaries after finishing 2nd.  the GOP has no clear cut front runner. At least half a dozen counties including Wayne,  Monroe and Oscoda. out of 83 do not have vote count. Look for an updated vote count a little later in the day.  Romney got nearly 39% votes (~337850) to McCain's 30% (257200) followed by Huckabee at 16% (~139700).

author.source: MICHIGAN DEPARTMENT OF STATE Bureau Of Elections
